We use a 5 $\times$ 5 grid of prototypes. The learning rate is fixed, as well as the neighbor radius. We train for 100 rounds (100 passes through the whole dataset).

In [6]:
prototypes_shape = jnp.array([5, 5])
learning_rate = 1e-1
neighbor_radius = 2
key = random.PRNGKey(0)
n_rounds = 100

som_res = somx.som_online(X,
                          prototypes_shape=prototypes_shape,
                          learning_rate=learning_rate,
                          neighbor_radius=neighbor_radius,
                          key=key,
                          n_rounds=n_rounds
                         )

The output of SOM gives us the topology of the SOM, the final prototypes, the history (values of the prototypes along the training), and the reconstruction error (along the training):

def animate_scatter(arrays, frames=10, auxil_scatter=None, auxil_color=None, xlim=None, ylim=None):

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, dpi=150)
    ax.set_xlim(xlim)
    ax.set_ylim(ylim)
    
    if auxil_scatter is not None:
        _ = ax.scatter(auxil_scatter[:,0], auxil_scatter[:,1], c=auxil_color)
    
    scatter = ax.scatter(arrays[0][:,0], arrays[0][:,1], c='r', ec='k')

    def animate(i):
        scatter.set_offsets(arrays[i])
        return scatter,
    
    anim = FuncAnimation(fig, animate, frames=frames)
    return anim
